SIMPLE: fix
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fix
<hw>Fix</hw> <pr>(f⟦icr⟧ks)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE., fr. L.
<ets>fixus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>figere</ets> to fix; cf. F.
<ets>fixe</ets>.]</ety> <def>Fixed; solidified.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fix</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fix
<hw>Fix</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Fixed</conjf> <pr>(f⟦icr⟧kst)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Fixing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>fixer</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To make firm, stable, or fast; to set or place
permanently; to fasten immovably; to establish; to implant; to secure;
to make definite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An ass's nole I <qex>fixed</qex> on his head.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O, <qex>fix</qex> thy chair of grace, that all my powers⟦br⟧
May also <qex>fix</qex> their reverence.</q>
<rj><qau>Herbert.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His heart is <qex>fixed</qex>, trusting in the Lord.</q>
<rj><qau>Ps. cxii. 7.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And <qex>fix</qex> far deeper in his head their stings.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To hold steadily; to direct unwaveringly; to fasten,
as the eye on an object, the attention on a speaker.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sat <qex>fixed</qex> in thought the mighty Stagirite.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One eye on death, and one full <qex>fix'd</qex> on heaven.</q>
<rj><qau>Young.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To transfix; to pierce.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sandys.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Photog.)</fld> <def>To render (an impression)
permanent by treating with a developer to make it insensible to the
action of light.</def> <rj><au>Abney.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>To put in order; to arrange; to dispose of; to
adjust; to set to rights; to set or place in the manner desired or most
suitable; hence, to repair; <as>as, to <ex>fix</ex> the clothes; to
<ex>fix</ex> the furniture of a room.</as></def> <mark>[Colloq.
U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <fld>(Iron Manuf.)</fld> <def>To line the hearth of (a
puddling furnace) with fettling.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To arrange; prepare; adjust; place; establish;
settle; determine.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fix</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Fix
<hw>Fix</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To become fixed; to
settle or remain permanently; to cease from wandering; to
rest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Your kindness banishes your fear,⟦br⟧
Resolved to <qex>fix</qex> forever here.</q>
<rj><qau>Waller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To become firm, so as to resist volatilization; to
cease to flow or be fluid; to congeal; to become hard and malleable, as
a metallic substance.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To fix on</b></col>, <cd>to settle the opinion or
resolution about; to determine regarding; <as>as, the contracting
parties have <ex>fixed on</ex> certain leading
points</as>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fix</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Fix
<hw>Fix</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A position of difficulty or
embarrassment; predicament; dilemma.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Is he not living, then? No. is he dead, then? No, nor dead either.
Poor Aroar can not live, and can not die, -- so that he is in an
almighty <qex>fix</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Iron Manuf.)</fld> <def>fettling.</def>
<mark>[U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fixable</ent>⟦br⟧
